This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it discusses the challenges of managing and analyzing large data sets produced by data centers. It also incorporates Big Data technologies such as Hadoop MapReduce and HDFS. 

The paper also discusses the use of SQL and R for analysis, which suggests that it may also belong to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. 

As the paper discusses the importance of identifying and resolving problems in data centers, it may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. 

The paper's focus on software and tool development suggests that it may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper's use of statistical analysis and machine learning techniques suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
